cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

The paper focuses on automated neural architecture search (NAS) for computer vision applications, specifically on improving the efficiency of one-shot NAS. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses Bayesian methods and optimization techniques, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence research, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper deals with neural networks and their architecture, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses object detection and person re-identification, which are subfields of computer vision and could fall under the category of cs.AR (Augmented Reality).
